  <div class="container">
    <p class="date"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> May 8, 2025</p>
    <p>Welcome to <span class="highlight">NishConnect</span> (“we”, “our”, or “us”). Your privacy is critically important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile and web application.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> We collect your full name, email address, phone number, and date of birth during registration. This information is used to create and manage your account, personalize your experience, and provide identity verification if needed.</li>
      <li><strong>Contacts Access:</strong> With your explicit permission, we access your phone’s contact list to identify and connect you with friends or known users already using NishConnect. We do not store your full contact list on our servers without consent, and access is solely used for in-app features like contact syncing and suggestions.</li>
      <li><strong>Messages and Chat Data:</strong> We collect and securely store your chat messages and multimedia content (e.g., photos, voice notes). All messages are encrypted end-to-end, ensuring that only you and the recipient can read them. This data enables chat history, message delivery, and sync across devices.</li>
      <li><strong>Call Logs and Communication Metadata:</strong> We may collect call-related data such as timestamps, duration, caller/receiver identifiers, and call status (missed, answered, declined) to provide features like call history and analytics. Actual audio or video from calls is not recorded or stored.</li>
      <li><strong>Device Information and Usage Data:</strong> We collect data such as device model, operating system, app version, IP address, crash reports, and diagnostic logs. This helps us troubleshoot issues, enhance security, and improve the overall app experience for users.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To deliver key features like messaging, voice calls, and contacts sync.</li>
      <li>To improve app performance, stability, and user experience.</li>
      <li>To notify users about app updates, messages, and new features.</li>
      <li>To enforce security, prevent abuse, and comply with legal requirements.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Information Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do <strong>not sell or rent</strong> your personal data. We may share limited data with trusted service providers (e.g., Firebase, hosting services) only for app functionality, and with legal authorities when required by law.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>All sensitive data is encrypted using industry-standard methods. Chats are end-to-end encrypted. Communications use TLS/SSL. Data is securely stored and access is restricted to authorized personnel only.</p>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your data as long as your account is active or needed for compliance, legal purposes, or app functionality. You may request data deletion by contacting us.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You may access, modify, or delete your personal data anytime by contacting us at <a href="mailto:oopsyvideos@gmail.com">support@nishconnect.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>NishConnect is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect information from them. If we learn that we have collected such data, we will delete it immediately.</p>

    <h2>8. Permissions Required</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contacts:</strong> Optional, for syncing and finding friends</li>
      <li><strong>Microphone:</strong> Required for voice calling</li>
      <li><strong>Internet:</strong> Required for messaging and sync</li>
      <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> Required to alert users of messages and calls</li>
      <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Optional, for sending/receiving media</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. Changes to this Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be notified via the app or email. Continued use of the app after updates implies your agreement to the revised policy.</p>

